external_knowledge:
- "Physical attributes" refer to the player's height and weight;
- "Origins" refer to the player's country of origin;
- "Team affiliations" refer to the team name;
- "League participation" refers to the league name;
- "Accolades" refer to the awards received by the player;
- "Seasons they were honored" refers to the years the awards were given;
- "Roster sizes" refer to the number of players in a team and league.

- "Shining stars" refers to top draft picks;
- "Recently drafted" refers to players drafted within the last 5 years;
- "Top 3 players" refers to the highest draft picks within each year.

- "wise elders" refers to players whose age is greater than the average age of players in the league;
- "team" refers to the group of players with `team_id = 1`;
- "league" refers to the group of players with `league_id = 0`.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(player_id) AS total_players
FROM players
WHERE league_id = 0 AND team_id = 1 AND age > (SELECT AVG(age) FROM players WHERE league_id = 0);

external_knowledge:
- "Blooming flowers" metaphorically represent players who have received at least one award;
- "Gardens" metaphorically represent teams;
- "Cumulative number" means the running total as we go through the list.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT p.league_id) AS total_leagues_with_awards
FROM players p
JOIN awards a ON p.player_id = a.player_id;

SELECT AVG(a.total_awards) AS average_awards_per_player
FROM (
  SELECT player_id, COUNT(award_id) AS total_awards
  FROM awards
  GROUP BY player_id
) a;

